## Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

**Is open source AI as secure as proprietary?**
When hosted correctly, open source AI is arguably *more* secure for enterprises. Because you host the model on your own servers or VPC, your sensitive data never travels to a third-party API provider, drastically reducing the risk of data leaks.

**What are the hidden costs of self-hosting Llama 3?**
While you save on API token fees, self-hosting requires significant expenditure on cloud compute (GPU instances like Nvidia A100s or H100s), as well as the engineering salaries required for MLOps, scaling, and maintaining the infrastructure.

**Will open source models eventually overtake proprietary models?**
It is heavily debated in the AI community. While proprietary models currently hold the absolute edge in reasoning capabilities, open source models are improving at a staggering rate, backed by massive communities and tech giants like Meta.

**Can I switch from a proprietary API to an open source model later?**
Yes, but it requires architectural changes. This is why many companies build an abstraction layer in their code, allowing them to route requests to OpenAI today and switch the endpoint to a self-hosted Llama 3 instance tomorrow without rewriting the core application.

